            <p>Please read the following questions carefully and provide complete answers.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Globally Unique -->
        <div class="form-field">
        <label for="guq">Globally Unique<span class="required">Required</span></label>

        <div class="input">
            <p>Do you need a globally unique address?</p>
            <ul class="inputs-list">
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="guq" value="yes" >
                    <span>Yes</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="guq" value="no" >
                    <span>No (Note: This option means that you can use a private use address, also known as administratively scoped address. 239.0.0.0/8 is set aside for this purpose, and a breakdown of the scope can be found in section 8 of <a href="/go/bcp23">BCP 23</a>)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <p>If you answered "Yes" and wish to proceed, explain why you need a globally unique address.</p>
                <textarea class="xxlarge" id="guq_usage" name="guq_usage" rows="2"></textarea>
            </ul>
        </div>
        </div>

        <!-- GLOP -->
        <div class="form-field">
        <label for="glop">GLOP<span class="required">Required</span></label>

        <div class="input">
            <p>Do you have an AS Number from the range 1-64495?</p>
            <ul class="inputs-list">
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="glop" value="yes" >
                    <span>Yes (This means that you already have 256 unique multicast addresses. Unless you have already used most of these addresses, you should make use of this <a href="/go/bcp53">GLOP space</a> before submitting this request.)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="glop" value="no" >
                    <span>No</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Please explain why you can not use GLOP.</p>
            <textarea class="xxlarge" id="glop_usage" name="glop_usage" rows="2"></textarea>
        </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RFC 6034 -->
        <div class="form-field">
        <label for="rfc6034">RFC 6034<span class="required">Required</span></label>

        <div class="input">
            <p>Do you have at least one unicast /24 of address space that is not tied to your upstream ISP?</p>
            <ul class="inputs-list">
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="rfc6034" value="yes" >
                    <span>Yes (Note: This means you already have a unique multicast address for each unicast /24 you have. See <a href="/go/rfc6034">RFC 6034</a>.)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="rfc6034" value="no" >
                    <span>No</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Please explain why you can not use RFC 6034.</p>
            <textarea class="xxlarge" id="rfc6034_usage" name="rfc6034_usage" rows="2"></textarea>
        </div>
        </div>


        <!-- SSM -->
        <div class="form-field">
        <label for="ssm">Source-specific Multicast<span class="required">Required</span></label>

        <div class="input">
            <p>Are you able to use Source-specific Multicast (SSM)?</p>
            <ul class="inputs-list">
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="ssm" value="yes" >
                    <span>Yes (Note: you should use SSM, see <a href="/go/rfc4604">RFC 4604</a> and <a href="/go/rfc4607">RFC 4607</a>)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="ssm" value="no" >
                    <span>No</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Please explain why it is not possible to use SSM.</p>
            <textarea class="xxlarge" id="ssm_usage" name="ssm_usage" rows="2"></textarea>
        </div>
        </div>


        <!-- Assignment Block -->
        <div class="form-field">
        <label for="block">Assignment Block<span class="required">Required</span></label>

        <div class="input">
            <p>In which block are you requesting an assignment?</p>
            <ul class="inputs-list">
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="block" value="localnetworkcontrol" >
                    <span>Local Network Control Block (<a href="/go/rfc5771">RFC 5771</a>, section 3)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="block" value="internetworkcontrol" >
                    <span>Internetwork Control Block (<a href="/go/rfc5771">RFC 5771</a>, section 5)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="block" value="adhoc" >
                    <span>AD-HOC Block (<a href="/go/rfc5771">RFC 5771</a>, Section 6)</span>
                    </label>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <label>
                    <input type="radio" name="block" value="other" >
                    <span>Other</span>
